# Day 11 — Dog Bowl

**Course day:** 11 of 30 · **Built:** 10 Jun 2026 · **Week:** 4

---

## What I built

A dog bowl modelled using surface tools — patch and stitch workflow to create the bowl shape, then thickened into a solid.

## Techniques used

- Surface Patch to create the curved bowl profile
- Stitch to close the surface into a watertight body
- Thicken to convert surface to solid with uniform wall thickness

## Key rules learned

- Patch fills an open boundary with a surface — all edges of the boundary must be connected for it to work
- Stitch requires all edges to be within tolerance — gaps cause it to fail
- Thicken direction matters: inward vs outward changes the final wall geometry

## Time taken

~40 min

## Files

- `dog-bowl.f3d` — Fusion 360 file
- `isometric.png` — clean isometric screenshot
